               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [On Thursday Baron von Mueller received a telegram from Mr. Uhr, police magistrate at Cloncurry, to the effect that Belooch's statement ¶  in regard to the alleged finding of the remains was so con...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.01.07</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Reginald Uhr</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Telegram not found. For the text given here, see <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg> (Melbourne), 9 January 1886, p. 32. See also <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 8 January 1886, p. 5.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[On Thursday Baron von Mueller received a telegram from Mr. Uhr, police magistrate at Cloncurry, to the effect that Belooch's statement<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Belooch to M, 5 January 1886.</p>
               </note> in regard to the alleged finding of the remains was so confused that he could making nothing of it, and that no reliance could be placed upon the report of the discovery.]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The text is accompanied by the following information: 'Baron von Mueller, while accepting this reply as matter of fact, has wired back to Mr. Uhr, asking him to acquaint him with anything further which may transpire in relation to the affair. No further news has yet been received from Belooch himself.' M's telegram not found.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to E. Strickland, 9 January 1886.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
